# Norr AI — environment template
# Copy to .env and fill in real values. .env is gitignored and protected by the
# block-env-edit.py hook. Never commit real secrets.

# ── Local development (this repo) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# The only variable this repo needs locally: the pooled Neon connection string,
# used for psql (`psql "$DATABASE_URL" -f db/schema.sql`) and the Neon MCP tools.
# Neon project `norrai` (gentle-hill-54285247), Postgres 17, db `neondb`, branch main.
# Use the POOLED connection string (host contains "-pooler").
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://<user>:<password>@<host>-pooler.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require

# ── Platform credentials — NOT stored here ─────────────────────────────────────
# The service keys below run the automation stack but live where the workflows
# run, not in this repo's .env. Listed for reference so their home is discoverable:
#
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY        → n8n Cloud credential (Claude API, all tiers)
#   SENDGRID_API_KEY         → n8n Cloud credential (email via hello@norrai.co)
#   TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID       → n8n Cloud credential (SMS; one subaccount per client)
#   TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN        → n8n Cloud credential
#   TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER       → n8n Cloud credential
#
# Cloudflare Pages/Workers deploys authenticate via `wrangler login` (or a
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN in the shell environment), not via this file.
